<h2><strong>Preparing Your Vehicle For Door to Door Delivery</strong></h2>
<ul>
 	<li>Check your battery, tire pressure, and fluid levels before shipping your automobile. Any mechanical faults or operating peculiarities should be notified to the car shipping firm before pickup.</li>
 	<li>Before transporting your car, be sure it has at most 1/4 tank of gas.</li>
 	<li>Before exporting an automobile, clean it thoroughly and remove any loose or personal objects. Removable car stereos, GPS systems, garage door openers, and parking permits fall under this category.</li>
 	<li>Remove non-retractable antennas, spoilers, luggage racks, or other car attachments.</li>
 	<li>If the alarm cannot be disarmed, send comprehensive instructions to the car transport firm on turning it off.</li>
 	<li>Before car delivery, document and photograph any existing vehicle damage for your records.</li>
 	<li>If your car is a convertible, raise the top. If this is not an option, <a href="https://rapidautoshipping.com/services/enclosed-shipping" target="_blank"><strong>enclosed transport</strong></a> by car shipping firms is a viable alternative that should be considered.</li>
 	<li>Give the driver of the car transportation firm a complete set of all vehicle keys.</li>
</ul>
